title: Square packing in a square
summary: Square packing in a square is a packing problem where the objective is to determine how many squares of side one (unit squares) can be packed into a square of side a {\displaystyle a} .  If a {\displaystyle a} is an integer, the answer is a 2 {\displaystyle a^{2}} , but the precise, or even asymptotic, amount of wasted space for non-integer a {\displaystyle a} is an open question.[1]
